definitions.definition: Of objects, the property of being coincident ; occurring at the same time or place .
Of events , the appearance of a meaningful connection when there is none.
examples: That the two writers were born and died on the same day is just a coincidence , although there are many conspiracy theories about it.
It is sheer coincidence that the cartoon resembles the local politician.

definitions.definition: A fixed point of a correspondence ; a point of a variety corresponding to itself under a correspondence.

main_definition: Of objects, the property of being coincident ; occurring at the same time or place .
